Comment: 1 thing that stopped GOT from being without a doubt the best series ever was them trying to save some money by not using all the great Characters from the Song of Ice and Fire. It also didnt make any sense why this happened. What I mean by this is From alot of Families characters were excluded. Mace Tyrell had 4 children not 2. Garlan was a great swordsman and Willas was smart and the Heir to Highgarden. I can understand not including both but atleast 1. High Born families prioritize having atleast 1 male heir and it made no sense to have the 1 Male Heir join the kingsguard bc someone needed to continue the Tyrell dynasty. Atleast Willas should have been included in the Show. The worst thing was they never used Dorne properly like Doran Martell had 3 children. Arianne had alot of potential and was his heir,Quentyn was the spare and had his uses. The Daynes never got any mention outside of the Brief scene in the Tower of Joy. Arthur had a big brother who had a son Aka Edric Dayne who was the Heir of Starfall plus Ashara who was among the most beautiful women in the realm. Final point after all the Starks that died in the Rebellion why would 1 of the 2 remaining Stark go to the wall where he would have no children instead of Marrying and continuing the Stark line as a cadet branch of the Starks. All that faulty logic held the series and books back from being even better.

Author: Vize Kommandant Reiner Braun
Comment:
There are gaps on that pikewall. Gaps that are quite easy enough to exploit. The formation isn't like the Macedonian phalanx, which was far more invincible and terrifying frontal formation, where each enemy soldier faces two sets of pikes (having the business end of the Macedonian phalanx of five ranks, making one enemy soldier face ten pikes in total) 

The Bolton shield/pike wall is far less from that. As I've said earlier, the gaps created created by those large shields are wide enough for each wildling or soldier to go through and exploit. That soldier could easily hack the spear-ends of the pikes with his sword and if he's strong enough, push the shield bearer in front of him and stab the other shield bearer on the side, then it creates a wider gap for them to exploit and destroy the pike wall.

"And who are you,"
the proud lord said,
"that I should bow so low?"

"Only a cat of a different coat!
That's all the truth I know."
"In a coat of gold, a coat of red,
a lion still has claws."

"And mine are long and sharp, my Lord.
As long and sharp as yours!"

And so he spoke, and so he spoke;
That lord of Castamere.
And now the rains weep o'er his hall,
with no one left to hear.

Yes, now the rains weep o'er his hall,
and not a soul to hear.

I'll take force of nature savage roar to the face or ice block freeze mage any day over things like rng lackeys and insane value cards like Hagatha. I don't want individual game swingy cards and random effects, i want decks that can be predicted and played around, because without that skill means very little. You can't play around "I got lucky enough to burgle the right card" or "i got the right spell from hagatha". I get that those things don't happen every game, but they should happen in zero games, not just "less than half".

My highlight of this Brawl was when I played the old Midrange Druid list against the fully optimized Jade Druid and absolutely slaughtered it because he couldn't handle Chillwind Yeti and Carine Bloodhoof.
